  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10971968/turning-sonar-off-for-certain-code",
  "title" : "Turning Sonar off for certain code",
  "body" : "<p>Is it possible to turn off sonar (<a href=\"http://www.sonarsource.org\" rel=\"noreferrer\">www.sonarsource.org</a>) measurements for specific blocks of code, which one doesn't want to be measured?</p>\n\n<p>An example is the \"Preserve Stack Trace\" warning which Findbugs outputs.  When leaving the server, I might well want to only pass the message back to the client, not including the actual exception which I just caught, if that exception is unknown to the client (because the client doesn't have the JAR in which that exception was contained for example).</p>\n"
